<br>
Dont like the rules?  Don't come.  It's honestly very, very simple.<br>
<br>
I shouldnt have to say much more than that, but I will, because evidently I need to justify myself *every* step of the way.<br>
<br>
I'm not keen on the idea of giving epic items to people who either arent motivated enough to start their epics (There's much more to the bard epic than just getting a White Scale, for instance) or maybe (Since there are better weapons for warriors) never plan on getting their epics (and thus will only sell the items).  And I can hardly say that not doing this is the opposite of NBG.  Who needs their white scale more?  wee little level 46 bard twink wearing leather who wont level past 48 or 49?  Or the primary or heavily played secondary (whatever, a char who gets a lot of played time) and is short one or two items aside the white scale?<br>
<br>
I reiterate.. dont like the rules, dont come.  Got a problem?  Plead your case with me, or just dont come.  I'm not going to change my mind just to satisfy one person while the truth is, Karliya and I are still learning what rules we have to make as we go along.  This is a process for us.  Not just a &quot;We kill stuff and give stuff to people&quot; thing.  Sorry, but it is a tad more structured than that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urolielkotn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RolielKotN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/2/02 5:41:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's our number one rule?</span><hr size=1> Kiradure is correct. There is more to the bard epic than simply getting a white and red scale. I've had both for about a month and a half now, and have not completed my epic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC=http://www.tiannathomas.com/images/roliel3.gif>
